@NODE "Introduction" "Introduction"

 Introduction
 ------------

 Chartist3D is a 3D chart generator. It takes CSV (ASCII) file as input and
 produces @{b}RPL script@{ub} which can be fed into @{b}Real3D@{ub}. One may ask what the #?*@
 CSV is? Fear NOT, my friend! It's an oridinary text file containing values
 separated with comma. There is one in 'Example' directory so if you are in
 doubt - look at it.

@ENDNODE

@NODE "SystemReq" "Requirements"

 Requirements
 ------------

 * Kickstart v2.0 or better.
 * Real3D v2 or higher (just in case you'd like to SEE your chart)

@ENDNODE


@NODE "Configuration" "Usage"

 Usage
 -----

 * Color Gradation

   If there is more than one line of data in your input file each one can
   have its own colour.

 * Column Separation

   Distance between columns. May vary from 0 to 200% the column's width.

 * Boundaries

   A simple trick to strenghten the 3D look. Also useful if you want to add
   description to your chart (see 'Preview.png').

 * Type

   Here you can choose from 6 predefined types. 'Polyhedron' is my
   favourite one.

 * Convert

   Requests an input file. Saving is automatic -- the '.rpl' suffix is
   appended to filename.

   That's all. Now it's Real3D turn.
   Use 'Project -> Macros -> Execute Named' to load your project.

@ENDNODE

